-- John Lewis Sales Rise 10% in Week to $191 Million on Beauty Products, Toys
-- B y   M i k e   H a r r i s o n
-- 2010-12-12T11:47:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-12/john-lewis-sales-rise-10-in-week-to-191-million-on-beauty-products-toys.html
John Lewis Partnership Plc said
weekly sales at its U.K. department stores rose 10 percent from
the year-ago period, driven by beauty products, toys and home
furnishings.  Sales were 121 million pounds ($121.2 million) in the week
to Dec. 11, the London-based company said in an e-mailed
statement today. The figure is a 16.7 percent increase on the
previous week.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mike Harrison at 
 mharrison5@bloomberg.net  